# Article Page Creation — Sitecore Marketer MCP

When creating article pages in Sitecore via the Marketer MCP, follow this guide. It consolidates learnings from travel article creation (Rhone River Cruises, Strasbourg Basel Upper Rhine) and the Saga Magazine style. Articles can cover **Travel**, **Entertainment**, **Home**, **Life**, or **Insurance** — each topic has its own folder under Magazine.

## Content Structure

Articles live under **Magazine** in saga-group, organised by topic:

```
/sitecore/content/saga-group/saga-group/Home/
  └── Magazine
      ├── Travel
      │   ├── Strasbourg Basel Upper Rhine
      │   ├── Rhone River Cruises
      │   └── <New Article>
      ├── Entertainment
      ├── Home
      ├── Life
      └── Insurance
```

**Topic folders:** Travel, Entertainment, Home, Life, Insurance. Create articles under the topic that matches the content.

**Resolve parent path first:**

```
get_content_item_by_path(itemPath="/sitecore/content/saga-group/saga-group/Home/Magazine")
# → magazineFolderId

get_content_item_by_path(itemPath="/sitecore/content/saga-group/saga-group/Home/Magazine/Travel")
# → travelFolderId (for travel articles)

get_content_item_by_path(itemPath="/sitecore/content/saga-group/saga-group/Home/Magazine/Entertainment")
# → entertainmentFolderId (for entertainment articles)

# Similarly: Home, Life, Insurance
```

If a topic folder does not exist, create it with the Folder template (`a87a00b1-e6db-45ab-8b54-636fec3b5523`) under Magazine.

## Article Page Template

- **Path:** `/sitecore/templates/Project/saga-group/Presentation/Article Page`
- **Template ID:** Resolve via `get_content_item_by_path`
- **Base:** Inherits from Page template (may include `_Seo Metadata` for SEO fields)

**Required fields:** Title, Excerpt, Content, MainImage, Author, PublishedDate

## Field Formats

### PublishedDate (critical)

Use **ISO 8601 format** — not `YYYY-MM-DD`:

```
"PublishedDate": "2026-02-22T00:00:00Z"
```

Plain `"2026-02-22"` may not persist correctly in Sitecore.

### Content (Rich Text)

HTML string with `<p>`, `<h2>`, `<strong>` etc. No manual quote escaping.

### Author

Use `"Saga Magazine"` for magazine-style articles (matches [Saga Magazine Travel](https://www.saga.co.uk/magazine/travel/which-greek-island-is-right-for-you)).

### MainImage

- **Standard format:** `'<image mediaid="{MEDIA-ITEM-GUID}" />'`
- **DAM format:** Some sites use `<Image src="..." dam-id="..." ... />` — match existing pages.

## Article Writing Style

Write in **magazine article style**:

1. **Title:** Engaging, descriptive (e.g. "Rhone River Cruises: Your guide to France's most scenic waterway")
2. **Excerpt:** Standfirst that draws readers in — 2–3 sentences covering key destinations and appeal
3. **Content structure:**
   - Intro paragraph (bold lead, then 1–2 sentences)
   - Section headings (`<h2>`) for each destination or theme
   - **"Best for:"** tagline under each section (e.g. "Best for: Food, culture, UNESCO heritage")
   - Descriptive paragraphs with specifics (names, places, experiences)
   - Closing section (e.g. "Why cruise with Saga — Spirit of the Rhone, savings, CTA)")

4. **Tone:** Conversational, engaging, not corporate. Use "we've got", "don't miss", "expect long, lazy days".

## SEO Fields

**Always set** when creating or updating article pages via `update_content`:

| Field | Purpose | Example |
|-------|---------|---------|
| MetaTitle | Search result title | "Article Title \| Saga Magazine" |
| CanonicalUrl | Canonical URL | `https://sagademo.vercel.app/saga-group/en/magazine/<topic>/article-slug` |
| OpenGraphTitle | Social sharing title | Same as article title |
| OpenGraphDescription | Social sharing description | Excerpt or shortened |
| OpenGraphImage | OG image (media XML) | Reuse MainImage if available |
| Robots | Indexing | `index, follow` |
| TwitterTitle | Twitter card title | Same as OpenGraphTitle |
| TwitterDescription | Twitter card description | Same as OpenGraphDescription |
| TwitterImage | Twitter card image (media XML) | Reuse MainImage |

## Create Article Page Flow

### 1. Resolve IDs

```
get_content_item_by_path(itemPath="/sitecore/content/saga-group/saga-group/Home/Magazine/<Topic>")
# Topic = Travel, Entertainment, Home, Life, or Insurance
get_content_item_by_path(itemPath="/sitecore/templates/Project/saga-group/Presentation/Article Page")
```

### 2. Create page

```
create_content_item(
  name="Article Name",
  templateId="<articlePageTemplateId>",
  parentId="<topicFolderId>",
  fields={
    "Title": "Display Title",
    "Excerpt": "Standfirst...",
    "Content": "<p>...</p><h2>Section</h2><p>...</p>",
    "Author": "Saga Magazine",
    "PublishedDate": "2026-02-22T00:00:00Z"
  }
)
```

### 3. Add page layout

```
add_component_on_page(
  pageId="<newPageId>",
  componentRenderingId="<articleImageMetaRenderingId>",
  placeholderPath="headless-main",
  componentItemName="Article Image Meta"
)
# Repeat for ArticleTitleExcerpt, ArticleContent
```

**Rendering IDs:** Resolve via `get_content_item_by_path`:
- `/sitecore/layout/Renderings/Project/saga-group/Article/ArticleImageMeta`
- `/sitecore/layout/Renderings/Project/saga-group/Article/ArticleTitleExcerpt`
- `/sitecore/layout/Renderings/Project/saga-group/Article/ArticleContent`

**Order:** article-image-meta, article-title-excerpt, article-content

### 4. Update SEO and PublishedDate

```
update_content(
  itemId="<pageId>",
  siteName="saga-group",
  fields={
    "PublishedDate": "2026-02-22T00:00:00Z",
    "MetaTitle": "Article Title | Saga Magazine",
    "CanonicalUrl": "https://sagademo.vercel.app/saga-group/en/magazine/<topic>/article-slug",
    "OpenGraphTitle": "Article Title",
    "OpenGraphDescription": "Excerpt text...",
    "Robots": "index, follow",
    "TwitterTitle": "Article Title",
    "TwitterDescription": "Excerpt text..."
  }
)
```

### 5. MainImage and OpenGraphImage / TwitterImage

Add MainImage when media is available. Use same image for OpenGraphImage and TwitterImage for social sharing.

```
# After uploading media
update_content(
  itemId="<pageId>",
  siteName="saga-group",
  fields={
    "MainImage": '<image mediaid="{MEDIA-GUID}" />',
    "OpenGraphImage": '<image mediaid="{MEDIA-GUID}" />',
    "TwitterImage": '<image mediaid="{MEDIA-GUID}" />'
  }
)
```

## URL Structure

With `[site]/[locale]/[[...path]]` routing:

- **Path:** `magazine/<topic>/<item-name-slug>`
- **Topics:** travel, entertainment, home, life, insurance (lowercase in URL)
- **Item name** "Rhone River Cruises" → slug `rhone-river-cruises`
- **Examples:**
  - Travel: `magazine/travel/rhone-river-cruises`
  - Entertainment: `magazine/entertainment/article-slug`
  - Life: `magazine/life/article-slug`
  - Insurance: `magazine/insurance/article-slug`

## Common Template IDs

| Template | ID |
|----------|-----|
| Article Page | Resolve via path |
| Folder | `a87a00b1-e6db-45ab-8b54-636fec3b5523` |
| JSON Rendering | `04646a89-996f-4ee7-878a-ffdbf1f0ef0d` |

## MCP Tools Used

- `get_content_item_by_path` — resolve IDs and paths
- `create_content_item` — create article page
- `update_content` — update fields (SEO, PublishedDate, MainImage)
- `add_component_on_page` — add article components to placeholder

## Publish

There is no MCP publish tool. Publish the page in XM Cloud Pages or via your deployment workflow so it appears on the site.

